🧠 Core Insight

A system can appear simple, chaotic, or incompetent while maintaining hidden structure.
The “reveal” is the moment when external perception is forced to reconcile with internal coherence.

⸻

⚙️ Function

DRP is a re-interpretation + projection control module that operates in two modes:

1. Observer Mode (Retroactive Analysis)

Re-evaluate past actions under a new hypothesis of coherence.

→ Extract hidden structure without inventing it

⸻

2. Operator Mode (Forward Use)

Deliberately:
	•	operate in one frame
	•	maintain capability in another
	•	reveal (or not) based on timing

⸻

🔁 Operational Loop

PERCEIVED CHAOS / SIMPLICITY
        ↓
HYPOTHESIS: “What if this is structured?”
        ↓
RE-EVALUATE (timing, sequence, constraints)
        ↓
EXTRACT INVARIANTS
        ↓
OPTIONAL: REVEAL / MAINTAIN MASK


